         <div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn">

            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi>
            </ab>

            <p>
               kō-vicaiya-kampa<unclear>va</unclear><hi rend="grantha">rmma</hi><unclear>k</unclear>ku yāṇṭu patiṉ ēḻ-<unclear>āvatu</unclear>
            </p>

            <p>
               <unclear>paṭuvūrkō</unclear>ṭṭattu-k kāvati-p-pāk
               <lb break="no" n="2"/>kam-ākiya Avaṉi-nārāyaṇa-c-catu<hi rend="grantha">rvveti</hi>-maṅkalattu-c ciṟṟampalattu-p peru-makkaḷ kaṭai
               <lb break="no" n="3"/>kāṭci-y-āka-t tiru-<unclear>vā</unclear>naṅkamuti tamakkai nampirāṭṭi viruttū<unclear>ṇar</unclear>kku
               vaitta poṉ <num value="736"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/></num>
               Ēḻu-<supplied reason="omitted">nū</supplied><choice><orig>tt</orig><reg>ṟṟ</reg></choice>u mu-p
               <lb break="no" n="4"/>-pat<unclear>t’ aṟu</unclear> kaḻañcu
            </p>

            <p>
               Ip-poṉṉāl vanta viruttiyāl nicati oru viruttūṇar uṇpat-āka vaittāḷ
            </p>

            <p>Itu
               <lb n="5"/><unclear>Ā</unclear>ca<hi rend="grantha">ndra</hi>kālamum muṭṭāmai Ūṭṭuvippat-āka-<unclear>y i</unclear>p-peru-makka<unclear>ḷ ka</unclear>ṭai-k kāṇpār āṉār</p>


            <p>
               It-ta<hi rend="grantha">rmma</hi>muṭṭil k<choice><sic>e</sic><corr>a</corr></choice>ṅkai-y-i-
               <lb break="no" n="6"/>ṭai-k kumari-y iṭai-c ceytār ceyta pāvam pa<unclear>ṭu</unclear>vār āṉār
            </p>

            <p>
               I<hi rend="grantha">d-dharmma<supplied reason="omitted">m</supplied> rakṣi</hi><supplied reason="omitted">t</supplied>tār kāl eṉ muṭi mēlaṉa
            </p>

         </div>

         <div type="apparatus">

            <listApp>

               <app loc="3">
                  <lem><num value="736"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/></num></lem>
                  <note>In <ptr target="bib:VenkatasubbaAyyar1943_01"/>'s edition two symbols are printed, apparently reproducing what is visible on the stone and looking like 100 and 1. <ptr target="bib:VenkatasubbaAyyar1943_01"/> notes: <cit><quote>This symbol probably stands for the figure 736.</quote></cit> As 736 <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s is a very unusual amount, an alternative reading could be: <foreign> {symbol=36} Eḻuttu</foreign>. The word <foreign>eḻuttu</foreign> would be preceded by the figure in symbol and by the same figures in letters.</note>
               </app>

            </listApp>

         </div>

         <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">

            <p n="1">
               Prosperity! Fortune!
            </p>

            <p n="1">
               Seventeenth year of the victorious king Kampavarman.
            </p>

            <p n="1-3">
               The gold that ... gave ...: seven hundred thirty-six <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s.
            </p>

            <p n="4">
               With the interest that came through this gold, she gave ...
            </p>

            <p n="4-5">
               This ...
            </p>

            <p n="5-6">
               If ...
            </p>

            <p n="6">
               The feet <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kāl</foreign><note>Note the use of the word <foreign>kāl</foreign>, instead of the usual word <foreign>aṭi</foreign>.</note></supplied> of he who protects this pious act are on my head.
            </p>


         </div>

